CatDescriptText: Image might relate to article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper November 17, 1945, pg. 2, with portions reading: "Twin Victory Week - Greater Pittsburgh Lodge Plans Double Celebration - A combined anniversary and mortgage burning celebration of the Greater Pittsburgh Lodge no. 115 and Ruth Temple No. 116, I.B.P.O.E. of W., will be observed in their home at 639 Lincoln Avenue during the week of Nov. 18 through 25th... Friday, Nov. 23, 8:30 P.M., Ruth Temple No. 116 will sponsor a Tin Pan Minstrel Show..."
TitMainTitle: Performers in "The Tin Pan Minstrel" wearing blackface and holding tin pans and drums, seated in front of audience in Elks Lodge No. 115 and Ruth Temple No. 116, 639 Lincoln Avenue, Larimer
